<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="239" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1185,1390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1257,1282]" pageId="9" pageNumber="239">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is easily recognized from the congeners in 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1009,1258,1281]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="239">Iran</collectingCountry>
by the yellow frons with a tiny black spot medially. Other species have either an almost all black frons or a black stripe medially on the frons.
</paragraph>
